**How to Run Real Franka Setup**

Terminal 1: Check Arm is ready
>> cd ws_franka_library/libfranka/build/
>> ./examples/echo_robot_state 172.16.0.2

(See robot at the Idle state)

Terminal 2: Run Franka Arm

For real arm
>> cd ws_robots
>> ros2 launch franka_moveit_config moveit_real_arm.launch.py robot_ip:=172.16.0.2
>> ros2 launch franka_moveit_config moveit_real_arm_platform.launch.py robot_ip:=172.16.0.2 camera_type:=blackfly_s serial:="'22141921'" load_camera:=True planner:=ompl_interface/OMPLPlanner
>> ros2 launch franka_moveit_config moveit_real_arm_platform.launch.py robot_ip:=172.16.0.2 camera_type:=blackfly_s serial:="'22141921'" load_camera:=True planner:=pilz_industrial_motion_planner/CommandPlanner
Test on fake arm
>> ros2 launch franka_moveit_config moveit_real_arm.launch.py robot_ip:=172.16.0.2 use_fake_hardware:=True
>> ros2 launch franka_moveit_config moveit_real_arm_platform.launch.py robot_ip:=172.16.0.2 use_fake_hardware:=True camera_type:=blackfly_s serial:="'22141921'" load_camera:=True planner_:=ompl_interface/OMPLPlanner

Terminal 3: Run High-Res Camera

>> cd ws_sensors
>> ros2 launch spinnaker_camera_driver driver_node.launch.py camera_type:=blackfly_s serial:="'22141921'" (included in moveit_real_arm_platform.launch.py)

Terminal 4: Run image processor for visualizing RGB image with color

>> ros2 run image_proc image_proc --ros-args --remap /image_raw:=/flir_camera/image_raw (may cause error)

Terminal 5: Run lattice sampler

>> cd ws_active_perception
>> ros2 launch viewpoint_generator lattice_publisher.launch.py 

Terminal 5: Run next_pose_commander for franka and image saver at each pose

>> cd ws_active_perception
>> ros2 launch moveit2_commander_recorder moveit_commander.launch.py 

To pause/resume pose commands to arm

>> ros2 service call /moveit_commander_node/pause_motion std_srvs/srv/Empty
>> ros2 service call /moveit_commander_node/resume_motion std_srvs/srv/Empty





